<dl>
        <dt>Tap the network manager indicator in the upper right-hand 
corner</dt>
                <dd>If you have a local wifi access point, you should
see it in the list</dd>
        <dt>Tap your wifi access point to connect to it</dt>
                <dd>If a passphrase or key is needed to associate with
your access point, you will need to enter it now</dd>
        <dt>Wait for the network manager indicator animation to stop and
show a successful connection</dt>
        <dt>Tap the icon for Firefox in the launcher</dt>
        <dt>Browse to some web pages (ex. http://www.ubuntu.com)</dt>
